derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from late Latin dualitas, from dualis (see dual)

entry.def: A duality is a situation in which two opposite ideas or feelings exist at the same time.

example.ex: We live in a world of duality, day and night, positive and negative, male and female, etc.
